The DirectionalSound (_dir) type is used to apply a small amount of spread and translation to a sound.

Fields:

InnerAngle - float value. Unknown
OuterAngle - float value. Unknown
RearAttentuation - float value. Unknown
YawAngle - float value. Unknown
PitchAngle - float value. Unknown

Example:

<Item type="DirectionalSound">
 <Name>sirens_slow_dir3</Name>
 <Header>
  <Flags value="0x00008000" />
  <Category>vehicles_sirens</Category>
 </Header>
 <ChildSound>sirens_slow_dir3_sirens_slow</ChildSound>
 <InnerAngle value="20" />
 <OuterAngle value="65" />
 <RearAttentuation value="-3" />
 <YawAngle value="90" />
 <PitchAngle value="0" />
</Item>